### Link to repro

https://github.com/aneesijaz/react-compiler-date-bug

### Repro steps

Just run the application. It's a minimal React app created with Vite, and the component is already rendered from App.tsx, so no additional setup is required beyond installing dependencies and starting the dev server.


**Code**
```tsx
import { useEffect, useState } from "react";

export const TimerComponent = () => {
  const [counter, setCounter] = useState(0);
  const time = (new Date()).getTime();

  useEffect(() => {
    const timer = setTimeout(() => setCounter(counter + 1), 1000);
    return () => {
      clearTimeout(timer);
    }
  }, [counter]);

  return (
    <div>{time} - {counter}</div>
  )
}
```

